ai_enrichment.traditional_solution:
Let the fraction be $\frac{x}{y}$.

The problem states that the numerator is doubled ($2x$) and then increased by $10\%$, and the denominator is tripled ($3y$) and then decreased by $30\%$.

An increase of $10\%$ means the value becomes $110\%$ of the original, and a decrease of $30\%$ means the value becomes $70\%$ of the original.

Thus, the new fraction is

$$
\frac{110\% \times 2x}{70\% \times 3y}
=
11\% \times \frac{16}{21}
$$

We can simplify the percentages and coefficients:

$$
\frac{1.10 \times 2x}{0.70 \times 3y}
=
\frac{2.2x}{2.1y}
$$

And the right side is

$$
\frac{11}{100} \times \frac{16}{21}
$$

Equating them:

$$
\frac{2.2x}{2.1y}
=
\frac{11}{100} \times \frac{16}{21}
$$

To isolate $\frac{x}{y}$, we multiply both sides by $\frac{2.1}{2.2}$:

$$
\frac{x}{y}
=
\frac{11}{100} \times \frac{16}{21} \times \frac{2.1}{2.2}
$$

Since $2.1 = \frac{21}{10}$ and $2.2 = \frac{22}{10}$, this becomes

$$
\frac{x}{y}
=
\frac{11}{100} \times \frac{16}{21} \times \frac{21}{10} \times \frac{10}{22}
=
\frac{2}{25}
$$

