$$

Solving for $\frac{x}{y}$:

$$
\frac{x}{y}
=
\frac{11}{100} \times \frac{16}{21} \times \frac{2.1}{2.2}
=
\frac{11}{100} \times \frac{16}{21} \times \frac{21}{22}
=
\frac{1}{100} \times 16 \times \frac{1}{2}
=
\frac{8}{100}
